Dow falls nearly 150 points on losses in shares of Goldman Sachs, Exxon Mobil

The Dow Jones Industrial Average is declining Friday morning with shares of Goldman Sachs and Exxon Mobil facing the biggest drops for the price-weighted average. Shares of Goldman Sachs GS, +0.09% and Exxon Mobil XOM, +4.43% are contributing to the blue-chip gauge's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, +0.52% was most recently trading 144 points, or 0.7%, lower. Goldman Sachs's shares have fallen $8.52, or 5.7%, while those of Exxon Mobil have dropped $1.49, or 4.3%, combining for an approximately 68-point drag on the Dow. Other components contributing significantly to the decline include 3M MMM, -0.03%, Pfizer PFE, -0.48%, and IBM IBM, +2.11%. A $1 move in any of the index's 30 components results in a 6.78-point swing.

